In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims March 25, 2010, as "Greek Independence Day: A National Day of Celebration of Greek and American Democracy." He emphasizes the ties between Greece and the United States as allies and friends. Obama recognizes the contributions of Greek Americans to the United States and highlights the influence of ancient Greece on American scholarly traditions. He mentions the Hellenic ideal of democracy, which continues to strengthen the bonds between the two nations. The President calls upon the people of the United States to observe this day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.